message: /* Criticism */Deleted fact-free nonsense stated with incorrect grammar (run-on sentence). Go has interfaces, short declarations with type inference, const declarations, and type switches. I suggest the author of this criticism first learn English, then learn Go.
/* See also */  ce - sort, clarify outdated link (1 link per line)
/* Design */ - Unclear what the "tradition of C" means. Use simpler wording.
/* C compilers */ C99/C11 support by GCC is partial due to floating-point issues (rounding direction). Or perhaps floating point needs to be excluded from this table, but this should be mentioned.
